<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="types">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Types.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Holotype ♂ (NMPC), 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">INDONESIA</emphasis>
. South Kalimantan: Kandagan distr., 17 km NE of Laksado vill., 900 m, 3-22.IX.1997, leg. S. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jákl">Jakl</normalizedToken>
. Paratypes. 11♂♂ (JBCB), same data as holotype; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">MALAYSIA</emphasis>
. Sabah: 2♂♂ (TARI), Trusmadi, 1.X.2014, leg. Y.-T. Wang; 2♂♂ (TARI), same but with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“2.X.2014”">&quot;2.X.2014&quot;</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Length 5.1-5.8 mm, width 1.8-2.3 mm. Body color (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Habitus of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. and B. kalimantanensis sp. nov. A B. jakli sp. nov., male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C B. jakli sp. nov., female, dorsal view D B. jakli sp. nov., male, color variation, dorsal view E B. kalimantanensis sp. nov., male, dorsal view F Same, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380681" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">26D-F</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, head and pronotum metallic green, prosternite dark brown, elytra yellowish but laterally and apically metallic green, antenna black except three basal antennomeres paler. Antennae filiform in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28A</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.3: 0.8: 0.9: 0.8: 0.8: 0.8: 0.8: 0.8: 0.7: 0.8, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 3.9: 1.8: 3.4: 4.4: 5.2: 5.3: 5.9: 5.8: 5.6: 4.6: 4.6. Elytra elongate, parallel-sided, 1.9-2.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; disc with dense, coarse punctures, arranged into longitudinal rows, with one indistinct longitudinal ridge between two longitudinal rows of punctures, with dense, short setae along ridges. Tarsomeres I of front legs slightly swollen in males. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28B-D</figureCitation>
) slender, 4.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; widest at basal 2/5, narrowed towards apical 1/7 and basal 1/5, parallel from apical 1/7 to apex, apical margin truncate, slightly depressed medially; tectum extremely slender, from apical 1/5 to basal 1/4; recurved in lateral view, angular at apical 1/6, straight from apical 1/6 to apex; ventral surface entirely sclerotized, triangular sclerites absent; internal sac with elongate endophallic sclerite, 0.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as aedeagus, apex with one pair of small processes directed ventrally, one pair of longitudinal rows of hair-like setae basally connected with apex of endophallic sclerite, one pair of lateral sclerites large and hook-like, subequal in length but with different apical shapes; basal opening medially closed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Variation.</emphasis>
Specimens from Sabah have slender lateral sclerites of the internal sac (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Bezdek, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Bezděk" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Borneotheopea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Borneotheopea kalimantanensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalimantanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Borneotheopea kalimantanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is easily distinguished from the other member of the genus, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., based on the distinct ridges on the elytra and yellowish brown ventral surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Habitus of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. and B. kalimantanensis sp. nov. A B. jakli sp. nov., male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C B. jakli sp. nov., female, dorsal view D B. jakli sp. nov., male, color variation, dorsal view E B. kalimantanensis sp. nov., male, dorsal view F Same, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380681" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">26E, F</figureCitation>
) (indistinct ridges on the elytra and metallic blue ventral surface in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Habitus of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. and B. kalimantanensis sp. nov. A B. jakli sp. nov., male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C B. jakli sp. nov., female, dorsal view D B. jakli sp. nov., male, color variation, dorsal view E B. kalimantanensis sp. nov., male, dorsal view F Same, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380681" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">26A-D</figureCitation>
). Males of B. 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="kalimantanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="kalimantanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">kalimantanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. are also easily separated from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the anterior directed apex and angular process at apical 1/6 of the aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28C</figureCitation>
) (the apex of aedeagus directed ventrally and without angular processes in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figure 27. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380682" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">27D</figureCitation>
)), extremely slender tectum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28B</figureCitation>
) (short and wide tectum in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figure 27. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380682" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">27C</figureCitation>
)), presence of clustered setae at apex of median elongate sclerite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 28" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figure 28. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea kalimantanensis sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Aedeagus, dorsal view C Aedeagus, lateral view D Aedeagus, ventral view E Aedeagus, dorsal view, from Sabah." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380683" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">28B, C</figureCitation>
) (without setae at apex of median elongate sclerite in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jakli" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="jakli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">B. jakli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figure 27. Diagnostic characters of Borneotheopea jakli sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380682" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">27C-E</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
